\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch   HOW IT WORKS}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
{\listtext\pard\fi-430\li720\bullet 	}\pard\plain{\ltrpar\ql\fi-430\li720\s28{\*\abilist\abilistid1007\abilistparentid0\abilistlevel1\abistartat0{\abifieldfont Nimbus Sans L}{\abilistdecimal NULL}{\abilistdelim %L}{\abiliststyle Bullet List}}{\*\pn\pnql\pnstart0\pnlvlblt{\pntxtb\bullet}}\ls1\ilvl0\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1040{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch Server side:}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
}\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1040{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch At first, the server takes map elevation and texture paths from terminal,  }{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}loads the images, configures TCP socket, provides to signal handling and initialize the world with the images loaded before.}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1040{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch The server main program continues with the initialization of TCP connection through a port number defined in }{\s28\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}common.h}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0} launching a thread that will be joined by the main program.}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch The function run by this thread (namely }{\s28\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}thread_server_tcp}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}) accepts every client connection and launches other two threads, }{\s28\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}client_thread_handler}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0} and }{\s28\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}udp_handler}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}, that will manage respectively clients\uc1\u8217\'92 requests (id, map elevation, map texture) and clients\uc1\u8217\'92 updates.}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch Every time that the server accept a client connection, it adds the client to a specific data structure, }{\s28\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}ClientList}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}, that contains all users connected, each one as a }{\s28\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}ClientListElement}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}.}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch Each user has a unique id, correspondent to his socket TCP descriptor.}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch Moreover, each user has its vehicle and the correspondent vehicle texture, received by the user itself through TCP communication.}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch Last but not least, every }{\s28\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}ClientListElement}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0} contains the user coordinates in the world, that are updated through UDP communication, and his rotational and translational forces.}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch In }{\s28\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}client_thread_handler}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}, the server waits for a }{\s28\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}GetId }{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}request from the client and answer with a }{\s28\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}GetId }{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}packet containing the id assigned to that client.}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch The second step consists in the receiving of }{\s28\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}GetTexture }{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}and }{\s28\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}GetElevation }{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}packets, that will be followed by an answer of type }{\s28\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}PostTexture }{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}and }{\s28\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}PostElevation}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}.}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch In the end, a }{\s28\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}GetVehicleTexture}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0} packet comes to notify that the client wants the vehicle texture of another user in the world.}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch The server answer with a }{\s28\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}PostTexture }{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}packet that contains that texture.}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch In }{\s28\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}udp_handler}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}, the server configures the UDP socket, with a port number defined in }{\s28\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}common.h.}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch After that, the server receives a }{\s28\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}VehicleUpdatePacket }{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}from the client and updates the user\uc1\u8217\'92s data structure contained in }{\s28\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}ClientList.}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch Moreover, the server sends a }{\s28\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}WorldUpdatePacket}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0} to every client in users list to update position, translational and rotational force of every user.}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch //Disconnection (eventually)}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch When a user comes off-line,  the server deletes its vehicle from the world and deallocates its data.}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch When the server is closed, it frees used resources, closes TCP socket, destroys the world and terminates.}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
{\listtext\pard\fi-430\li720\bullet 	}\pard\plain{\ltrpar\ql\fi-430\li720\s28{\*\abilist\abilistid1011\abilistparentid0\abilistlevel1\abistartat0{\abifieldfont Nimbus Sans L}{\abilistdecimal NULL}{\abilistdelim %L}{\abiliststyle Bullet List}}{\*\pn\pnql\pnstart0\pnlvlblt{\pntxtb\bullet}}\ls2\ilvl0\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch Client side:}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
}\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch At the beginning, the client takes IP address and vehicle texture path from terminal, loads this image, provides to signal handling and configures TCP connection.}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch After that, it connects to server and sends }{\s28\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}GetId}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}, }{\s28\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}GetElevation}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}, }{\s28\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}GetTexture }{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}requests, to receive id, map elevation and map texture of the world, and a }{\s28\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}PostTexture}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0} packet containing its vehicle texture.}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch After having initialized the world and added its vehicle to it, the client main program configures socket UDP and creates two threads (}{\s28\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}sender_udp }{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}and }{\s28\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}receiver_udp}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}).}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch At the end of the main program, the game is opened in a new window.}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch The }{\s28\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}sender_udp }{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}thread provides to send }{\s28\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}VehicleUpdatePacket }{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}to communicate vehicle\uc1\u8217\'92s movements to server.}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch The }{\s28\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}receive_udp }{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}thread, instead, receives }{\s28\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}WorldUpdatePacket }{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}to update the client\uc1\u8217\'92s world:}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch - if a vehicle isn\uc1\u8217\'92t in the world, the client launches a }{\s28\f0\fs24\i\lang1033{\*\listtag0}get }{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}thread to add the new user in the world with its vehicle;}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch - else if a vehicle exists, the client updates its position in the world;}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch - at the end, the client removes disconnected clients with their vehicles from the world;}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch - //Disconnection (eventually).}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch When the client is closed, the used resources are released, TCP and UDP socket are closed and it terminates.}{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s28\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\s28\f0\fs24\lang1033{\*\listtag0}\par}
